{{for|the practice of phasing out obsolescent technologies|Deprecation}}
'''Self-deprecation''' is the act of reprimanding oneself by belittling, undervaluing, or disparaging oneself,<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.thefreedictionary.com/Self-deprecation | title = Self-deprecation | accessdate = 2010-06-08 | work = The Free Dictionary | publisher = Farlex}}</ref> or being excessively modest.<ref name= dictionary>[http://personalityspirituality.net/articles/the-michael-teachings/chief-features/self-deprecation/ Self-Deprecation - Personality & Spirituality<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>[http://dictionary.reference.com/browse/self-deprecation Self-deprecation | Define Self-deprecation at Dictionary.com<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref> It can be used in humor and tension release.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hill|first=Matthew|title=The Funny Thing About Work|publisher=Society for Intercultural Training and Research|url=http://www.sietar.org.uk/publications/articles/55-the-funny-thing-about-work|accessdate=2011-05-04}}</ref>
Self-deprecation is often perceived as being a characteristic of certain nations, such as Great Britain, Ireland, Australia and New Zealand, where "[[Vanity|blowing one's own trumpet]]" is frowned upon.<ref name="Debrett's">{{cite web | url=http://www.debretts.com/british-etiquette/british-behaviour/r-s/self-deprecation | title=Self-Deprecation | publisher=Debrett's | accessdate=4 May 2014}}</ref> Famous examples include Irish comedian Ruairi Culleton and English comedian [[David Mitchell (comedian)|David Mitchell]]. It is also seen as a major component of the comedy of American comedians such as [[Rodney Dangerfield]], [[Phyllis Diller]], [[Joan Rivers]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.boston.com/ae/theater_arts/comedy/articles/2010/06/20/the_many_faces_of_joan_rivers/ | work=The Boston Globe | first=Wesley | last=Morris | title=The many faces of Joan Rivers | date=2010-06-20}}</ref> [[Louis C.K.]], [[Don Knotts]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.legacy.com/obituaries/washingtonpost/obituary.aspx?n=don-knotts&pid=16845505 |title=Don Knotts Obituary: View Don Knotts's Obituary by The Washington Post |publisher=Legacy.com |date=2006-02-25 |accessdate=2013-07-01}}</ref> [[Woody Allen]],<ref>{{cite web|last=Forward |first=The |url=http://www.haaretz.com/news/is-self-deprecation-killing-jewish-comedy-1.277679 |title=Is self-deprecation killing Jewish comedy? - Israel News &#124; Haaretz Daily Newspaper |publisher=Haaretz.com |date=2009-06-10 |accessdate=2013-07-01}}</ref> [[Zach Galifianakis]], [[Mike Birbiglia]], [[Carrot Top]], and [[Conan O'Brien]].


